about.summary: Python binding to chemfiles, a modern library for chemistry file reading and writing

name: chemfiles-python
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.9.1" %}
{% set sha256 = "90ed58776b6ff6470120fe0faa8473d565745f8fd4db56ed17814077767c703a" %}

package:
  name: chemfiles-python
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: chemfiles.py-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://github.com/chemfiles/chemfiles.py/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}
  patches:
    - cmake.patch

build:
  skip: true  # [win and py2k]
  number: 0
  script: >
    {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv --install-option="--generator=Ninja" --install-option="--skip-generator-test"

requirements:
  build:
    # Build time dependencies
    - cmake
    - pip
    - scikit-build
    - wheel
    # Run time dependencies
    - python
    - enum34  # [py2k]
    - numpy
    - chemfiles-lib 0.9.*
  run:
    - python
    - enum34  # [py2k]
    - numpy
    - chemfiles-lib 0.9.*

test:
  source_files:
    - tests/
  commands:
    - python -m unittest discover -p "*.py" tests

about:
  home: http://chemfiles.org
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  summary: Python binding to chemfiles, a modern library for chemistry file reading and writing
  doc_url: http://chemfiles.org/chemfiles.py/latest/
  dev_url: https://github.com/chemfiles/chemfiles.py

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - luthaf
